
Overview of adj forgetful

The adj forgetful has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                       
1. (1) unretentive, forgetful, short -- ((of memory) deficient in retentiveness or range; "a short memory")
2. unmindful, forgetful, mindless -- (not mindful or attentive; "while thus unmindful of his steps he stumbled"- G.B.Shaw)
3. forgetful, oblivious -- (failing to keep in mind; "forgetful of her responsibilities"; "oblivious old age")
